Tower of Babel. Witt Library. Under Hendrick van Cleve. Paintings, all derived from Boymans Bruegel: 1) Hamburg; 2) Sale Mak van WAAY, A'dam, 10 May 1971 (N° 38) Then with the de Boer; 3) Sale, Lempertz, Cologne, 20-22 April 1967, N° 803; 4) Kröller-Müler, Mus.Otterloo, on copper, (Siècle de Bruegel, N° 63, pl. 184); 5) Mossel Sale, Müller, A'dam 11-18 March, 1952 (668); Drawing: Museum Pomorskie, Gdansk (see Connoisseur March 1962); Under Martin van Cleve: Sale Giroux, 25-27 June 1954, N°26.
